Preheat the oven to 220°C. Drain and rinse the @chickpeas{1%400g can} in a #sieve{}. Pop the chickpeas and @cauliflower florets{300%g} on separate #baking trays{}, sprinkle both with @ground turmeric{1%tsp}, drizzle with @olive oil{2%tbsp} and season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}. Toss to coat then spread out and roast cauliflower on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{18-20%minutes}. Roast the chickpeas on the middle shelf of your oven until slightly crispy, ~{5%minutes}. Once the chickpeas are cooked, remove from your oven and set aside to cool.

Meanwhile, fill and boil your #kettle{}. Put the @couscous{120%g} in a #bowl{}. Put the @chicken stock powder{1%tsp} in a #measuring jug{}, stir in the @water{240%ml}(boiling) and pour into the bowl, cover tightly with #cling film{} and leave to the side for ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve.

Heat #medium frying pan{} over medium heat (no oil!) Once hot, add the @flaked almonds{15%g} and cook, stirring regularly, until lightly toasted, ~{1-2%minutes}.

> TIP: Watch the almonds like a hawk as they can burn easily.

Once toasted remove from the pan and transfer to a #small bowl{} (no need to wash your pan).

Put your #frying pan{} back on medium high heat with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tbsp} (no need to wash). Once hot, add the @chorizo{60%g} and fry until crispy, for ~{1-2%minutes}. Add the @dried cranberries{30%g} and fry briefly until warmed through, ~{1%minute}. Pop the chorizo and cranberries in a small bowl, along with any oil from the pan.

Pick the @mint{1%sprig} leaves from their stalks and roughly chop (discard the stalks). Zest and halve the @lemon{1/2}. Once the couscous is ready, stir with a #fork{} to separate the grains and add the @zoog style paste{50%g}, lemon zest and half the mint, mix well. Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed. Add a squeeze of lemon juice and the @olive oil{1%tbsp} to the cranberry chorizo mixture. Mix together, taste and season with salt and pepper.

Divide the couscous between #plates{}. Spoon on the roasted cauliflower and chickpeas. Drizzle the cranberry chorizo dressing and finish with a scattering of the toasted almonds and remaining mint. Serve with a lemon wedge. Enjoy!